// =============================================================================
// core.math.frameworks — trusted-axiom packages for external mathematical frameworks
// =============================================================================
//
// This module postulates key results from external formal-mathematics
// frameworks as @framework-tagged axioms. Every axiom carries an explicit
// citation so `verum audit --framework-axioms` can enumerate the trusted
// boundary of any proof that depends on them.
//
// The six packaged frameworks are:
//
//   lurie_htt               — Lurie, "Higher Topos Theory" (2009).
//                             Presentability, ∞-topos formation, adjoint
//                             functor theorem in the ∞-categorical setting,
//                             accessible categories, Kan extensions.
//
//   schreiber_dcct          — Schreiber, "Differential cohomology in a
//                             cohesive ∞-topos" (arXiv:1310.7930).
//                             Cohesive modalities, super-cohesion,
//                             rheonomy, the differential-cohesive hexagon.
//
//   connes_reconstruction   — Connes–Chamseddine (2008). Spectral
//                             reconstruction of smooth Riemannian manifolds
//                             from real spectral triples.
//
//   petz_classification     — Petz, "Monotone metrics on matrix spaces"
//                             (1996). Classification of quantum Fisher
//                             information metrics by operator-monotone
//                             functions.
//
//   arnold_catastrophe      — Arnold–Mather, catastrophe normal forms
//                             for codimension ≤ 4 (A_k, D_k, E_6/7/8).
//
//   baez_dolan              — Gordon–Power–Street (1995) / Baez–Dolan
//                             coherence for tricategories and higher
//                             n-category theories.
//
// Every use of one of these axioms in downstream code surfaces as an
// entry in `verum audit --framework-axioms`. The kernel's AxiomRegistry
// stores each axiom's FrameworkId (framework, citation), and any
// .verum-cert export carries the dependency list along.
//
// See docs/verification/framework-axioms for the full story.

public mount core.math.frameworks.lurie_htt;
public mount core.math.frameworks.schreiber_dcct;
public mount core.math.frameworks.connes_reconstruction;
public mount core.math.frameworks.petz_classification;
public mount core.math.frameworks.arnold_catastrophe;
public mount core.math.frameworks.baez_dolan;
